RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 5 Furlongs on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALLOTROPE led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, dug in while drifting in in upper stretch and just held the win. BOARDWALK QUEEN stalked the pace setter on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the bend from the three path, began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground quickly late to just miss. MISS POLO BAR raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend, improved position in upper stretch, raced in tight quarters near the eighth pole when ALLOTROPE drifted in and chased on on from there. CLIMB TO GLORY chased the leader on the inside early, came around the turn in the two path and kept on to the wire. THIS DAMSEL MAYFLY raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and showed no kick. MISSY PIGGY trailed the field on the outside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and made no bid. THE RIDER OF HORSE TWO, MISS POLO BAR, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE SEVEN, ALLOTROPE, CITING INTERFERENCE IN MIDSTRETCH. UPON REVIEW, THE CLAIM WAS ALLOWED AND HORSE SEVEN, ALLOTROPE, WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED THIRD FOR INTERFERENCE.

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Polo Bar
ENTRY.OWNER: Slam Dunk Racing and Silva Jr Jose

ENTRY.NAME: Climb to Glory
ENTRY.OWNER: Cipperley Devin M and Cipperley Steve

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 78. Allowance Purse 32000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY HOUR BOBBY bobbled leaving the gate, led the way on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and began to tire towards the wire but held the win. MIDNIGHT ROYAL raced off the pace on the outside early, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and gained ground steadily late. BIRDIE MACHINE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the turn and improved position in the lane. WITHSTANDTHESTORM pressed the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and was outkicked in the final furlong. WIN OVER WYATT raced off the pace between horses through the opening quarter, came around the bend in the three path and made no bid. SAM SEZ raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 101. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile O r Over Since June 27 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $40,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a dist ance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THAT'S NOT FUNNY saved ground around the firs turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, swung out to the four path to began a bid coming off the far turn and edged clear in the lane. STAGECOACH BOYS raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn, was caught in upper stretch and chased on to the finish. THOUGHT raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, navigated the second turn from the three path and finished evenly. CASHANOVA raced in the two path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, saved ground around the far turn and gained ground mildly in the stretch. TEMPTED MISSION dueled on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the far turn and faded in the lane. PAPA RIZZO raced in the two path early, dueled on the outside up the backstretch and around the far turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since June 27 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $40,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it wi ll be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOCK IT DOWN raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn and kicked clear. GYPSY WIFE saved ground while fighting her rider and racing into traffic two separate times in the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and gained ground late. LATIN NIKKITA raced off the pace on the inside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and improved position in late stretch. SWANAGE saved ground early, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and weakened late. DESERT GLOW raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JANUARY 27 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 27 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claiming Race s For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUNAWAY A. TRAIN led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and pulled clear in the lane. SAILSINTHESUNSET stalked the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the turn from the three path and kept on to the wire. FLASH FLOOD chased the pace setter on the outside early, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend and could not go with the winner in the stretch but kept on to the finish. BRAHMS IS WHO stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and weakened in the lane. SUNDANCE STAR pressed the pace between horses early, saved ground around the turn and was outkicked in the final furlong. LILA'S LUCKY LADY trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. PEPPERMINT SISTER hopped up leaving the gate, recovered to track the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and flattened out in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Peppermint Sister
ENTRY.OWNER: Biehler Michael E and Biehler Lori

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 27, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAKE NOISE raced in the three path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, drew off from the two path coming around the far bend and won in hand. BARNFIELD saved ground early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and gained ground late but was no match for the winner. BEAT THE HEAT hit the gate and was off slowly, saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and showed no kick. SARGE'S SERMON chased the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the bend from the two path and faded in the stretch.
